data.title: Meta's Global Affairs Chief Slams EU AI Code, Calls It A Burden On 'Western Open Source AI Models'
data.description: In a recent development, Meta Platforms Inc. (NASDAQ: FB) has decided not to comply with the European Union's AI Code of Practice. Joel Kaplan, the new head of global affairs at Meta, made this announcement, escalating the company's ongoing disputes with European regulators.

data.title: Sundar Pichai Downplays DeepSeek Threat — Google's Gemini Still Leads In Cost, Performance, And Latency
data.description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai acknowledged China's DeepSeek as a strong AI competitor but emphasized that Gemini models still lead in cost efficiency, performance, and scalability.

data.title: Tesla Rival Figure AI Ends Collaboration With OpenAI After 'Major Breakthrough,' Says It Will Show 'Something No One Has Ever Seen On A Humanoid' In Next 30 Days
data.description: Robotics company Figure AI is leaving its collaboration agreement with OpenAI following a 'major breakthrough' on its in-house robot AI, company CEO Brett Adcock said in a social media post on Tuesday.
